data.title: Au Navy 5420
data.meta_description: AU-NAVY-5420 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Sailors from the Royal Australian Navy's VIP Boat Squadron played a key role in transporting Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip across Lake Burley Griffin in Canberra during their historic royal visit to Australia. The three sailors navigated the Admiral's Barge carefully and received praise from the Queen for providing a lovely journey. Though transporting members of the royal family was a special occasion, the sailors said it was just another day carrying out their important role escorting dignitaries.
